Higher-point functions 
The method of brane running is completely general and can be extended to arbitrary order
point functions. The computation of  and higher-point functions is complicated in the AdS/CFT correspondence
because it involves bulk-to-bulk AdS propagators. In our case,
the structure of the differential equations for the
higher-point functions is similar to the case of the point
function and can be readily understood in a diagrammatic way.

